# MonEx Save, Sync & Reward Integrity (FROZEN)

These rules are **non-negotiable** for any work touching saves, sync, release, rewards, quests, party/box, activity recovery, or cloud persistence.

## Product policy (locked)

| # | Policy | Rule |
|---|--------|------|
| 1 | Save model | **Whole save for now.** One-action server APIs (release, catch, battle claim, quest claim) for critical mutations — do not build a second save system. |
| 2 | Recovery | **Only for new or broken accounts** — first login, empty/partial box, or obvious missing catches. **Never** run full activity re-import on every Party/Box open or poll forever. |
| 3 | Release connectivity | **Online only.** Release counts only after the server confirms. No offline release that syncs later. |
| 4 | Multi-device | **Newest save wins** via monotonic **revision** — not `updatedAt` alone. |
| 5 | Mon identity | **Every Mon gets a permanent unique instance ID** at creation/load. Never identify Mons by species name or array index alone. |
| 6 | Release location | **Box only — never Party.** One Mon at a time (no bulk release unless explicitly requested later). |
| 7 | Battle & quest grants | **Server claim APIs only** for rewards (battle win, quest task, chest, mailbox, shop). Logged-in users must not rely on local grant + autosave. |
| 8 | Reward connectivity | **Online only.** A reward counts only after the server confirms and returns updated save. |
| 9 | Campaign quest milestones | **Progress auto-updates on stage reach; reward requires manual Claim** in Daily Quest → Campaign. UI must not imply auto-grant. |
| 10 | Victory / claim UX | **Never show success with zero rewards** when server claim failed. Show error and allow refresh/retry. |

## Source of truth

- Cloud/KV save is **authoritative**. Client and localStorage are caches.
- After every successful server mutation (release, battle claim, quest claim, etc.), **apply the server-returned save** to client state and revision.
- Never fix persistence or reward bugs by hiding items in the UI, client-only counters, timeouts, or refresh loops.

## Single save pipeline

- There is **one** cloud save pipeline. Do not add a conflicting second save system.
- `play/index.html` `buildSavePayload()` and `js/auth-client.js` `buildSavePayload()` **must stay identical** in fields that affect gameplay.
- Never silently drop: `party`, `box`, `releaseLog`, `releasedRecoveryIds`, quests, mailbox, economy fields, or revision metadata.
- **Full-save PUT is not a reward path** for logged-in users. Grants go through dedicated claim endpoints.

## Release (Box only)

- Use **`POST /api/release-mon`** via `MonExRelease.releaseMon()` — the only release mutation path.
- Release by **`instanceId`** (or `wildPendingId` for X-caught Mons), never species or index alone.
- **Await server success** before treating release as done.
- **Roll back UI** and show an error if the server rejects or fails.
- **Disable release button** and guard against duplicate requests while in flight.
- Call **`MonExAuth.cancelPendingCloudSave()`** before release so stale autosaves cannot overwrite it.
- Releasing one Mon of the same species must not remove another instance.

## Rewards & claims (frozen)

### Server-authoritative grant paths (only these)

| Action | Client | Server endpoint |
|--------|--------|-----------------|
| Adventure / patrol win | `MonExBattle.claimBattleReward*` | `POST /api/battle/claim-reward` |
| Quest task (incl. campaign c1–c7) | `MonExQuest.claimQuestTask` | `POST /api/quest/claim-task` |
| Quest chest | `MonExQuest.claimQuestChest` | `POST /api/quest/claim-chest` |
| Release Mon | `MonExRelease.releaseMon` | `POST /api/release-mon` |
| Mailbox / shop / chest / packages | respective `*-client.js` | respective `/api/*` claim routes |

### After every successful claim

1. `applyLoadedSave(result.save)`
2. `writeLocalSave(result.save)`
3. Update header currencies / quest UI from applied save
4. `MonExAuth.setSaveRevision(result.save.revision)`

### Before every claim mutation

- Call **`MonExAuth.cancelPendingCloudSave()`** so stale debounced autosaves cannot overwrite the grant.

### Revision conflict retry (mandatory pattern)

- On `revision_conflict`, **re-apply the intended reward/progress delta** onto the latest cloud save.
- **Never** retry by writing raw latest save and dropping the grant (battle rewards, quest claims, release).
- Use merge helpers (e.g. `mergeBattleClaimOntoLatest`) — do not duplicate this pattern under a new name.

### Context for battle claims

- Adventure claims must send **chapter + stage** (or parse from `claimId` like `adv-{ch}-{st}-*`) so rewards are not computed from a load-sanitized stale playhead.
- Validate stage is reachable: `globalProgress <= adventureGlobalBest + 1`.

### Quest campaign milestones

- Server **`syncCampaignQuestProgress`** must **upsert** missing campaign task rows — never skip because task is missing.
- Client **`syncCampaignQuestProgress`** must create missing tasks the same way.
- Failed quest claim must **show an error** — never silent `return` with no user feedback.

### UI honesty (no fake success)

- Logged-in battle win: **forbidden** to show VICTORY with all-zero drops when server claim failed.
- **Forbidden** to grant gold/essence/XP locally for logged-in wins without server OK.
- Idempotent `alreadyClaimed` responses must still display the reward from the receipt.

## Background sync & recovery

- Autosave, poll, hydrate, activity recovery, and tab refresh **must not restore** intentionally released Mons or undo confirmed grants.
- Maintain append-only **`releasedRecoveryIds`** and **`releaseLog`** on the server; merge never drops them.
- **`stripReleasedMonsFromInventory`** (and activity recovery skip) must stay enforced on all write paths.
- Ignore or reject client/sync responses that would re-add Mons in the release blocklist or revert confirmed server grants.
- Stale full-save PUTs with a current `baseRevision` but old party/box/economy **must not** overwrite newer mutations.

## Concurrency

- All save writes use **revision / expectedRevision** where applicable.
- Serialize per-user mutations that grant or remove inventory (release lock, sync lock).
- Autosave must push **fresh** state (`setLiveSaveProvider`) after awaiting in-flight saves — never push a captured stale snapshot with an updated revision.
- Older in-flight saves lose to newer confirmed mutations.

